**Project Overview**

â™  Database Nexus is a unified, type-safe database framework for Python that provides a consistent interface across different database systems while preserving their unique capabilities. It combines the power of Pydantic validation, SQL flexibility, and NoSQL scalability into a single developer-friendly package.

**Key Features**

 â—‹ _Unified Models: Single model definition works across PostgreSQL, SQLite, MongoDB, Redis_

 â—‹ _Type Safety: Full IDE support with type hints and validation_

 â—‹ _Smart Migrations: Built-in migration system with automatic schema detection_

 â—‹ _Performance Insights: Built-in query profiling and N+1 detection_

 â—‹ _Multiple Database Support: Work with different databases using the same API_

 â—‹ _Async/Support: Native async support with sync compatibility_

**Supported Databases**

 â—‹ SQLite: [sqlite:///database.db](sqlite:///database.db)

 â—‹ PostgreSQL: [postgresql://user:password@localhost/dbname](postgresql://user:password@localhost/dbname)

 â—‹ MySQL (coming soon)

 â—‹ MongoDB (coming soon)

 â—‹ Redis (coming soon)

